26/03/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Despite a meeting between their prime ministers, the positions of Macedonia and Greece remained far apart regarding their long-standing name dispute.
Macedonia's Nikola Gruevski and Greece's George Papandreou met in Brussels on Thursday (March 25th).
Afterward, Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki said such meetings contribute to improving the overall atmosphere even if a solution is not yet at hand.
(MIA, Makfax - 25/03/10)
